I believe they cast Darksteel. While it is indestructible (from shattering, breaking, bending, etc) it does seem to still have a melting point it it gets hot enough ([Into the Core](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Into the Core), two [Darksteel Juggernaut](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Darksteel Juggernaut)s getting killed) or if treated with some unknown, naturally occurring chemicals ([Ferrovore](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Ferrovore), mentions it's digestion of [Darksteel Myr](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Darksteel Myr)s). So it makes sense to me that they just melt it down and fill molds with it.  

@Lueseto  
No more than any other artifact would. [Tarmogoyf](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Tarmogoyf) ability says it is equal to the number of types and 'Fortification' is a subtype, much like 'Equipment'. Unless you are asking about the tap trigger. Then yes, of course you can target your goyf to pump it.

